cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper proposes a statistical analysis framework for brain functional connectivity using a metric-based approach and dimensionality reduction technique. This involves processing large-scale and high-dimensional data from the Human Connectome Project database. The methodology involves clustering and classification of FC trajectories, which suggests a machine learning approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analyzing brain connectivity, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves processing and analyzing imaging data, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
